div.p:
He is altogether vanity, Kol Hebel Kol Adam;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
univerſae vanitas omnis homo; all men are all vanity, ſo it is word for word: the Septuagint render it, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , quoad omnia vanitas; the verſion of the Arabick thus, quicquid pertinet ad hominem viventem eſt vanum; whatſoever belongeth unto living man, is vanity.
